# Project Context

This context is automatically injected into every LLM prompt (all advisors, local and cloud).
Place a `HIVE.md` file in your project root to provide shared context.

## How it works

- `HIVE.md` in your project root → injected into every query
- `~/HIVE.md` → user-level context (applies everywhere)
- `~/.hive/global_context.md` → global context (lowest priority)
- `.hive/context/*.md` → modular context files for specific topics

## Example for a student project:

```markdown
# CS261 Data Structures Project

## Context
- Language: Java 17
- Build system: Gradle
- Testing: JUnit 5
- This is a university assignment — explain concepts, don't just give answers

## Rules
- Always explain the time complexity of solutions
- Prefer readable code over clever one-liners
- Follow Google Java Style Guide
- When debugging, explain WHY the bug occurs, not just how to fix it

## Current Assignment
- Implementing a red-black tree with insert, delete, and search
- Due: April 15, 2026
- Must handle duplicate keys by storing in a linked list at each node
```

## Example for a game development project:

```markdown
# Dragon Quest Clone — Game Design Context

## Tech Stack
- Engine: Godot 4.3
- Language: GDScript + some C# for performance
- Target: Steam (PC) + Nintendo Switch

## Design Principles
- Turn-based combat with party of 4
- Pixel art style (16x16 tiles, 32x32 characters)
- No microtransactions — premium $19.99

## Current Sprint
- Implementing the magic system
- Each spell has: element, mana cost, cast time, area of effect
- Need to balance damage formulas
```

## Frontmatter Options

| Field | Default | Description |
|-------|---------|-------------|
| `name` | filename | Display name for the context |
| `scope` | `all` | When to inject: `all`, `convene`, `query`, `code` |
| `priority` | `10` | Higher priority = injected first (0-100) |
